# Environment variables for HeliCoach

# Google Analytics Measurement ID
# Get this from Google Analytics dashboard
VITE_GA_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# Google Drive API credentials
# Get these from Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 1. Create a new project or select existing
# 2. Enable Google Drive API
# 3. Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID credentials (Web application)
# 4. Add authorized JavaScript origins (e.g., http://localhost:5173, https://yourdomain.com)
# 5. Add authorized redirect URIs (same as origins)
# 6. Create an API key and restrict it:
#    - HTTP referrers: Add your domain(s)
#    - API restrictions: Only allow Google Drive API
#
# SECURITY NOTE: Both values below are SAFE to commit to public repos and expose
# in client-side code when properly restricted in Google Cloud Console. The Client
# ID is designed to be public, and the API Key is protected by referrer + API
# restrictions. User data is protected by the OAuth consent flow, not these values.

# OAuth 2.0 Client ID (safe to expose when restricted to authorized origins)
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=YOUR_CLIENT_ID.apps.googleusercontent.com

# API Key (safe to expose when restricted to specific referrers + APIs)
VITE_GOOGLE_API_KEY=YOUR_API_KEY
